== 製作 ==
=== 籌備 ===
[[File:Wes_Anderson-20140206-85.jpg|缩略图]]
《歡迎來到布達佩斯大飯店》的故事草稿於2006年開始，當時[[魏斯·安德森|魏斯·安德森]]與長期合作人{{tsl|en|Hugo Guinness|雨果·堅尼斯}}創作了一份長達18頁的劇本<ref name="filmmag">{{Cite web |url=https://filmmakermagazine.com/84877-wes-anderson-on-using-throwback-ratios-romantic-worldviews-and-european-reconnaissance-to-craft-the-grand-budapest-hotel/#.XYFSn4wpCfA |title=Wes Anderson on Using Throwback Ratios, Romantic Worldviews, and European Reconnaissance to Craft The Grand Budapest Hotel |last=Oselund |first=R. Kurt |date=2014-03-08 |website=Filmmaker |dead-url=no|archive-url=https://archive.today/20190917214510/https://filmmakermagazine.com/84877-wes-anderson-on-using-throwback-ratios-romantic-worldviews-and-european-reconnaissance-to-craft-the-grand-budapest-hotel/%23.XYFT2tLLfK5 |archive-date=2019-09-17 |access-date=2019-09-17}}</ref>。他們以一個共同朋友為靈感創作一個角色，並以此構想出一齣支離破碎的故事，背景發生在現代法國和英國<ref name="Seitz31">{{harvnb|Seitz|2015|p=31}}</ref><ref name="collider">{{Cite web |url=https://collider.com/wes-anderson-the-grand-budapest-hotel-interview/ |title=Wes Anderson Talks The Grand Budapest Hotel, the Film's Cast, His Aesthetic, Shifting Aspect Ratios, and More |last=Weintraub |first=Steve |date=2014-02-24 |website=[[Collider|Collider]] |dead-url=no |archive-url=https://archive.today/20190915200109/https://collider.com/wes-anderson-the-grand-budapest-hotel-interview/ |archive-date=2019-09-15 |access-date=2019-09-15}}</ref>。儘管他們創作的的原型可以粗略剪一條12分鐘的影片<ref name="db">{{Cite news |url=https://www.thedailybeast.com/wes-anderson-takes-us-inside-the-grand-budapest-hotel-his-most-exquisite-film |title=Wes Anderson Takes Us Inside 'The Grand Budapest Hotel,' His Most Exquisite Film |last=Stern |first=Marlow |date=2014-03-04|newspaper=[[每日野獸|The Daily Beast]] |dead-url=no|archive-url=https://archive.today/20190917213650/https://www.thedailybeast.com/wes-anderson-takes-us-inside-the-grand-budapest-hotel-his-most-exquisite-film |archive-date=2019-09-17|access-date=2019-09-17}}</ref>，但安德森和堅尼斯因無法合併統一的事件順序來推進故事而使這項合作計劃停滯不前<ref name=collider />。到這個時候，安德森由於對奧地利小說家[[斯蒂芬·茨威格|-{zh-cn:斯蒂芬·茨威格;zh-tw:史蒂芬·褚威格;}-]]的作品依稀有印象，所以開始研讀它們。他被-{zh-cn:茨威格;zh-tw:褚威格;}-深深吸引，並著迷於《{{tsl|en|Beware of Pity (novel)|同情之罪|-{zh-cn:心灵的焦灼;zh-tw:同情之罪;}-}}》、《[[昨日的世界|昨日的世界]]》和《{{tsl|en|The Post Office Girl|變形的陶醉}}》當中[[宿命論|宿命論者]]的神話以及-{zh-cn:茨威格;zh-tw:褚威格;}-所描繪20世紀初的[[維也納|維也納]]<ref name="tele1">{{Cite news |url=https://www.telegraph.co.uk/culture/film/10684250/I-stole-from-Stefan-Zweig-Wes-Anderson-on-the-author-who-inspired-his-latest-movie.html |title='I stole from Stefan Zweig': Wes Anderson on the author who inspired his latest movie |last=Prochnik |first=George |date=2014-03-08 |website=[[每日電訊報|The Telegraph]] |dead-url=no|archive-url=https://archive.today/20140308120101/http://www.telegraph.co.uk/culture/film/10684250/I-stole-from-Stefan-Zweig-Wes-Anderson-on-the-author-who-inspired-his-latest-movie.html |archive-date=2014-03-08 |access-date=2019-09-15}}</ref><ref name="influence">{{Cite news |last=Perez |first=Rodrigo |url=https://www.indiewire.com/2014/03/interview-wes-anderson-on-the-grand-budapest-hotel-elliott-smith-the-beatles-owen-wilson-westerns-more-248448/ |title=Interview: Wes Anderson On 'The Grand Budapest Hotel,' Elliott Smith, The Beatles, Owen Wilson, Westerns & More |date=2014-03-05 |work=IndieWire |access-date=2019-09-15|dead-url=no |archive-url=https://archive.today/20190915232204/https://www.indiewire.com/2014/03/interview-wes-anderson-on-the-grand-budapest-hotel-elliott-smith-the-beatles-owen-wilson-westerns-more-248448/ |archive-date=2019-09-15}}</ref>。安德森還參考了舊時照片和以歐洲城市為背景的20世紀好萊塢喜劇<ref name=ind2 /><ref name="Seitz32">{{harvnb|Seitz|2015|p=32}}</ref>。由於他從主流媒體對前[[第二次世界大戰|第二次世界大戰]]歐洲歷史的理想化清醒過來，所以最終以一條另類的時間線來追求一齣歷史{{tsl|en|pastiche|仿品}}<ref>{{Cite web |url=https://www.npr.org/2014/03/12/289423863/wes-anderson-we-made-a-pastiche-of-eastern-europes-greatest-hits |title=Wes Anderson: 'We Made A Pastiche' Of Eastern Europe's Greatest Hits |last=Gross |first=Terry |date=2014-03-12 |website=[[NPR|NPR]] |dead-url=no|archive-url=https://archive.today/20190916012700/https://www.npr.org/2014/03/12/289423863/wes-anderson-we-made-a-pastiche-of-eastern-europes-greatest-hits |archive-date=2019-09-16|access-date=2019-09-15}}</ref>。當《歡迎來到布達佩斯大飯店》正式定型，安德森重新開始創作，並花了6週完成劇本<ref name=db />。製片人敲定傑·克拉克（{{lang|en|Jay Clarke}}）來指導電影[[分鏡|影像分鏡]]製作，而安德森為此配音<ref>{{Cite web |url=https://www.motionpictures.org/2018/02/berlinale-2018-storyboard-artist-jay-clarke-drawing-wes-andersons-canine-showstopper-isle-dogs/ |title=2018: Storyboard Artist Jay Clarke on Drawing Wes Anderson's Canine Showstopper Isle of Dogs |last=Edelbaum |first=Susannah |date=2018-02-20 |website=[[美國電影協會|Motion Picture Association]] |access-date=2019-10-26 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20191026133205/https://www.motionpictures.org/2018/02/berlinale-2018-storyboard-artist-jay-clarke-drawing-wes-andersons-canine-showstopper-isle-dogs/ |archive-date=2019-10-26 |dead-url=no }}</ref><ref name=db />。

在視覺主題上的另一個靈感是來自安德森遊覽歐洲的經歷<ref name="Seitz102">{{harvnb|Seitz|2015|p=102}}</ref>。導演在構思作品前參觀了維也納、[[慕尼黑|慕尼黑]]和其他主要城市，但大部分勘景是在他成長劇情片《[[月升王国|-{zh-tw:月昇冒險王國;zh-hk:小學雞私奔記;zh-hans:月升王国;}-]]》的[[第65届戛纳电影节|坎城影展]]首映會之後進行。他和製片人遊覽匈牙利[[布达佩斯|布达佩斯]]、義大利[[温泉镇|水療小城]]、捷克度假勝地[[卡罗维发利|卡罗维发利]]以及德國<ref name=Seitz102 />，並諮詢酒店的工作人員來對現實禮賓部人員的工作有個準確概念<ref name=db />。

=== 選角 ===
《歡迎來到布達佩斯大飯店》當中全體的17位演員皆為著名的演員<ref name="billing">{{Cite web |url=https://www.hollywoodreporter.com/news/wes-andersons-grand-budapest-hotel-648978 |title=Wes Anderson's 'Grand Budapest Hotel' to Hit Theaters in Spring |last=McClintock |first=Pamela |date=2013-10-16 |website=[[好萊塢報導|The Hollywood Reporter]] |dead-url=no|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20191101012833/https://www.hollywoodreporter.com/news/wes-andersons-grand-budapest-hotel-648978 |archive-date=2019-11-01 |access-date=2019-10-31}}</ref>。安德森慣常找一群長期的合作人參演——比爾·莫瑞、阿德里安·布罗迪、艾德華·諾頓、歐文·威爾森、蒂妲·絲雲頓、哈維·凱托、威廉·達佛、傑夫·高布倫和傑森·薛茲曼都曾出現在他的一部或多部作品中<ref>{{Cite news |last=Strassberg |first=Rebecca |url=https://www.backstage.com/magazine/article/actors-wes-andersons-troupe-9945/ |title=11 Actors in Wes Anderson's Troupe |date=2014-12-26 |work=Backstage |access-date=2019-10-31 |dead-url=no|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20191101010912/https://www.backstage.com/magazine/article/actors-wes-andersons-troupe-9945/ |archive-date=2019-11-01 }}</ref>。諾頓和-{zh-hans:莫瑞;zh-hk:梅利;zh-tw:莫瑞;}-在收到劇本後立刻簽約<ref>{{Cite web |url=https://entertainment.ie/cinema/movie-news/edward-norton-talks-all-things-wes-anderson-and-the-grand-budapest-hotel-241217/ |title=Edward Norton talks all things Wes Anderson and The Grand Budapest Hotel |last=Staff |date=2014-03 |website=Entertainment.ie |dead-url=no|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20191114182921/https://entertainment.ie/cinema/movie-news/edward-norton-talks-all-things-wes-anderson-and-the-grand-budapest-hotel-241217/ |archive-date=2019-11-14 |access-date=2019-11-14}}</ref><ref>{{Cite web |url=https://www.heyuguys.com/interview-bill-murray-the-grand-budapest-hotel/ |title=The HeyUGuys Interview: Bill Murray, Jeff Goldblum and Willem Dafoe on The Grand Budapest Hotel |last=Pape |first=Stefan |date=2014-03-07 |website=HeyUGuys |dead-url=no |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20191114182402/https://www.heyuguys.com/interview-bill-murray-the-grand-budapest-hotel/ |archive-date=2019-11-14 |access-date=2019-11-14}}</ref>。《歡迎來到布達佩斯大飯店》的群演大部分都是[[友情客串|客串]]<ref>{{Cite web |url=https://www.vulture.com/2014/02/wes-anderson-and-cast-on-grand-budapest-hotel.html |title=Wes Anderson, Bill Murray, and Tilda Swinton Explain The Grand Budapest Hotel |last=Siegel |first=Miranda |date=2014-02-06 |website=New York |dead-url=no |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20191114180051/https://www.vulture.com/2014/02/wes-anderson-and-cast-on-grand-budapest-hotel.html |archive-date=2019-11-14 |access-date=2019-11-14}}</ref>。由於這些角色的局限性，所以-{zh-cn:布罗迪; zh-tw:布洛迪; zh-hk:保迪;}-表示最顯著的挑戰是讓電影的喜劇元素以及其他的嚴肅主題保持平衡<ref>{{Cite news |last=Needham |first=Adam |url=https://www.theguardian.com/film/2014/mar/02/adrien-brody-oscar-roman-polanski-pianist-wes-anderson |title=Adrien Brody: life after the Oscar |date=2014-03-02 |work=The Guardian |access-date=2019-11-14 |dead-url=no |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20191114234458/https://www.theguardian.com/film/2014/mar/02/adrien-brody-oscar-roman-polanski-pianist-wes-anderson |archive-date=2019-11-14 |publisher=Guardian Media Group}}</ref>。除-{zh-hans:斯温顿;zh-tw:絲雲頓;zh-hk:史雲頓;zh-mo:史雲頓;}-之外，所有演員都是電影製片人的第一選擇。原本他們期望[[安吉拉·蘭斯伯里|-{zh-cn:安吉拉·兰斯伯瑞; zh-tw:安潔拉·蘭斯貝瑞; zh-hk:顏芝拉·蘭絲比利;}-]]來飾演D夫人，但她因事先接下《[[为黛茜小姐开车|-{zh-hans:为黛茜小姐开车; zh-tw:溫馨接送情; zh-hk:山水喜相逢;}-]]》的舞台劇版而放棄角色<ref>{{Cite web |url=https://www.sbs.com.au/movies/article/2014/04/10/grand-budapest-hotel-wes-anderson-interview |title=The Grand Budapest Hotel: Wes Anderson interview |last=Barlow |first=Helen |date=2014-04-10 |website=Special Broadcasting Service |dead-url=no|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20191114152723/https://www.sbs.com.au/movies/article/2014/04/10/grand-budapest-hotel-wes-anderson-interview |archive-date=2019-11-14 |access-date=2019-11-14}}</ref><ref name=conflict />。演員一旦被錄用後，製片人就會鼓勵他們研究電影原始資料來作準備<ref name=Ny2 />。從安德森的角度來看，-{zh-cn:达福;zh-tw:達佛;zh-hk:達福;}-和-{zh-hans:费因斯;zh-hk:費恩斯;zh-tw:范恩斯;}-特別認為影像分鏡有助於將《歡迎來到布達佩斯大飯店》概念化<ref name=Ny2 /><ref name=Seitz67 />。儘管-{zh-cn:达福;zh-tw:達佛;zh-hk:達福;}-不常談起它們，卻說：「因為你會想『好吧，他自有計劃』，所以它們十分有用。然而你不會想靠分鏡來演出。你只想要依靠當下的感受。」<ref name=Ny2 />

